        "content": "<p>Hello! Very new to Lean4. (Is this even the right place to post newb questions?) Have worked my way through Natural Number Game and read a decent chunk of manuals and ... getting completely lost the moment I try to apply to my own problems.</p>\n<p>I want to formalise a proof of \"some statement is divisible by X\" (e.g. <code>n^3 + 11*n</code> is divisible by 2). Where should I be looking for examples/documentation of builtins for working with modulus? (Searching gets confused with \"module\" I think.) I've found the operators <code>%</code> and <code>\\==</code> and <code>3 | ...</code> but I'm not sure which is preferred, where it's documented, and what tactics are available. I'm getting lost &amp; confused.</p>",
